obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2335  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Overexpression of LAR interfering constructs reduces the number of excitatory synapses\"\nFig.3: \"LAR interfering constructs decrease the density of dendritic spines\"\nFig.4: \"RNAi knockdown of LAR-RPTP reduces the density of synapses and spines\"\nFig.5: \"Effects of dominant-negative LAR constructs on synaptic function\". Experimental description: Dissociated neurons are from rat species: \"We report that LAR-RPTP is concentrated in mature synapses in cultured rat hippocampal neurons...\"\n\nOverexpressed protein is of human species: \"Anti-LAR mAbs against the extracellular region of LAR were generated by immunizing mice and screening hybridomas with transfected murine cell lines that expressed either the human LAR protein...\" (traced back to PMID:1547787)\n\n15/01/2018 Pim\n- Annotation to rat species was made based on RNAi data on rat neurons." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2335" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

